What is Linux? linkThe Linux kernel was created by Linus Torvalds in 1991. It becomes an operating system with the addition of components like a package manager, desktop environment, shell, and bootloader.
As an open-source OS, Linux offers numerous customizations. Each unique combination of these customizations is called a distribution or &ldquo;distro.&rdquo;
There are hundreds, if not thousands, of distros worldwide, each optimized for specific purposes or created just for fun by enthusiasts.
